Getting around XMLHttpRequest's Same Origin Policy can be a pain. This example repo shows three techniques for dealing with it: JSONP, CORS and Proxying using node.

To run, you'll need to install node.

$ git clone git@github.com:johnboxall/remote-api-js.git
$ cd remote-api-js
$ npm install
$ node index.js

Browse to http://127.0.0.1:8000/_/index.html.

